The Governor of Rivers State, Nyesom Wike has approved the appointment of an comedian, Yibo Koko as the Director-General of the Rivers State Tourism Development Agency. A statement signed by the Secretary to the State Government, Dr Tammy  Danagogo, says that the appointment takes immediate effect. Koko is the initiator of the popular Seki Dance. Rivers gov appoints Muslim pilgrims board’s sole administrator Yibo Koko is now head production Africa Magic Rivers govt sacks 344 lecturers